@node MULTITEXT_HISTORY "multitext_plugin: History"


    @{b}v1.0@{ub}                                   (2.10.97)

    o   Initial release.


    @{b}v1.1@{ub}                                   (28.10.97)

    o   Added text justification (left, right & center).

    o   Some sources using this module may need to be changed;
        the calling parameters of the initial method have been
        modified.

    o   Removed some unnecessary code from the render() method.


    @{b}v1.2@{ub}                                   (28.11.97)

    o   Rewritten to follow Ralph Wermke's PLUGIN Style Guide.

    o   Added the ability to disable the text field.

    o   Changed 3D mode, and added ability to draw bars (duplicates
        the functionality of the now defunct @{b}title_plugin@{ub}).


    @{b}v1.3@{ub}                                   (25.2.98)

    o   Changed a number of the tags (no point in having most
        of them @{FG shine}get()@{FG text}'able).

    o   Added rendering of multiple lines of text; this will
        require changes in sources already using this module.

    o   Changed name from @{b}text_plugin@{ub} to @{b}multitext_plugin@{ub}.


    @{b}v1.4@{ub}                                   (25.3.98)

    o   Added new tags:     @{FG shine}PLA_MultiText_ShowWhenDisabled@{FG text}
                                (this was suggested by Piotr Gapinski)
                            @{FG shine}PLA_MultiText_Resize@{FG text}
                            @{FG shine}PLA_MultiText_GapHorizontal@{FG text}
                            @{FG shine}PLA_MultiText_GapVertical@{FG text}


   @{b}v1.5@{ub}                                   (25.5.98)

    o   Minor bug fix: if EG_FONT was used in the main GUI and
        @{FG shine}PLA_MultiText_Font@{FG text} was not set, @{b}multitext_plugin@{ub} was not
        using the font set in EG_FONT on redraws, the screen font
        was used instead. All OK now.

@endnode
 
